# Figma Adaptation Priority Policy

Default behavior for UI implementation in this repository:

- Prioritize `shadcn` primitives and existing project conventions over direct pixel-perfect Figma replication.
- Treat Figma designs as reference input to be adapted into the current component system and tokenized styling.
- Reuse components from `app/components/ui` first, then extend with shadcn-compatible primitives if needed.

Use direct Figma style preservation only when the user explicitly asks for one of these intents:

- "Keep Figma style as-is"
- "Implement exactly like Figma"
- Equivalent explicit instruction to preserve Figma visuals over existing system patterns

When the user provides code and asks to "adapt to our structure":

- Refactor to project standards (`Vue 3 + script setup + Tailwind tokens + shadcn-first`)
- Preserve behavior and intent while aligning naming, structure, and styling with the codebase conventions
